dc_title_s: The countye palatine of Chester : comitatus Cestrensis / Amstelodami, Apud Ioannem Ianssonium.; The covntye palatine of Chester: comitatus Cestrensis;County of Chester;Cheshire
dc_description_s: Relief shown pictorially. Title cartouche in upper left has a farmer [huntsman?] and his dog on one side and a noblewoman with a goblet on the other. Bottom right corner has scale and a cherub. This state was published in atlases by Jan Jansson in 1636 and 1637. From the Jansson Appendix Atlas 1636-1680, title created to represent a unique collection within the Clark Library, University of Michigan. 1 map ; 37 x 48 cm. This map is in the public domain. Please attribute access and use of this digitized map to the Stephen S. Clark Library, University of Michigan Library.
